'@title start is now @event_start and end is now @event_end - Do you want to save this change?'
A view plugin to present contents in FullCalendar view.
CSS classes for further customization of this view.
Create a new event via the Off-Canvas dialog.
Current active language on the page
Fixed initial date displayed when the calendar first loads.
For specifying the end time of each recurring event instance. The field value should be a string in the format hh:mm:ss.sss, hh:mm:sss or hh:mm. For example, "05:00" signifies 5 hours.
If this option is selected, a confirmation dialog will pop-up after dragging and dropping an event.
If this option is selected, calendar events are allowed to overlap (default).
If this option is selected, day/week names will be linked to navigation views.
If this option is selected, editing by dragging and dropping an event will be enabled.
If this option is selected, the description (the last field in the fields list) will show in a dialog window once clicking on the event.
If this option is selected, there will be an Add Event link below the calendar that provides the ability to create an event In-Place.
In order to specify colors for event taxonomies, you must select a taxonomy reference field for the View.
Left side buttons. Buttons are separated by commas or space. See the %fullcalendar_doc for available buttons.
Limits the number of events displayed on a day. The rest will show up in a popover.
Open entities (calendar items) into new tabs
Render contents in Full Calendar view.

See %momentjs_doc for available formatting options.
Leave it blank to use the default format "hh:mm a".
Set it to [ ] if you do not want Fullcalendar View to prepend Title Field with any time at all.
Set color value of legends for each content type or each taxonomy.
Show event description in dialog window.
Shown as buttons on the right side of the calendar view. See the %fullcalendar_doc.
Source of the initial date displayed when the calendar first loads.
Specify colors for each bundle type. If taxonomy color is specified, this settings would be ignored.
Specify which vocabulary is using for calendar event color. If the vocabulary selected is not the one that the taxonomy field belonging to, the color setting would be ignored.
The bundle (content) type of a new event. Once this is set, you can create a new event by double clicking a calendar entry.
The default view must be one of the selected display toggles.
Time Format settings for month view
